00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:52,145 --> 00:00:53,065
You really don't remember me?

2
00:00:53,665 --> 00:00:54,825
Wait!

3
00:00:54,905 --> 00:00:56,265
Fun was my first love, you know.

4
00:00:58,145 --> 00:00:59,345
Krit?

5
00:00:59,425 --> 00:01:00,225
Yes.

6
00:01:00,305 --> 00:01:01,305
Again?

7
00:01:01,385 --> 00:01:03,905
<i>I have a meeting tonight</i>
<i>with the client Krit set up.</i>

8
00:01:03,985 --> 00:01:05,465
If you join my team,

9
00:01:05,545 --> 00:01:08,065
<i>I guarantee you'll earn a lot.</i>

10
00:01:11,425 --> 00:01:13,505
Krit actually said that to you?

11
00:01:15,865 --> 00:01:18,625
I don't know if he was serious or joking.

12
00:01:19,985 --> 00:01:23,145
I don't think he's a good person.

13
00:01:23,905 --> 00:01:29,465
Fun, the project you're doing with him
is almost done, right?

14
00:01:31,105 --> 00:01:32,825
It wraps up in the middle of next month.

15
00:01:35,065 --> 00:01:36,785
But…

16
00:01:36,865 --> 00:01:41,265
I just took on a new project
with him yesterday.

17
00:01:43,665 --> 00:01:45,105
Fun.

18
00:01:48,105 --> 00:01:52,145
Can you not do it? I'm worried.

19
00:01:54,425 --> 00:01:56,665
I don't want you
involved with him anymore.

20
00:02:00,505 --> 00:02:01,905
I already accepted it.

21
00:02:05,145 --> 00:02:07,425
We've even scheduled
a meeting with the client.

22
00:02:12,945 --> 00:02:15,465
But don't worry.

23
00:02:15,545 --> 00:02:18,585
I'll have Jess go with me.
I won't go alone.

24
00:02:23,385 --> 00:02:24,665
Good.

25
00:02:26,825 --> 00:02:29,025
I don't trust that guy at all.

26
00:02:33,585 --> 00:02:35,185
Trust me, okay?

27
00:02:36,545 --> 00:02:41,185
I'm always careful, and I never give him
a chance to get close.

28
00:02:44,025 --> 00:02:46,225
I always trust you.

29
00:02:47,505 --> 00:02:49,705
I never doubted you.

30
00:02:52,745 --> 00:02:57,745
But still, be extra careful, okay?

31
00:02:59,465 --> 00:03:00,505
Okay.

32
00:03:47,265 --> 00:03:48,185
Hey!

33
00:03:48,265 --> 00:03:50,585
Hey there, Auntie.

34
00:03:50,665 --> 00:03:52,745
When did you get back?

35
00:03:59,985 --> 00:04:01,625
Why didn't you tell me?

36
00:04:02,785 --> 00:04:05,585
-Nueng!
-Hey there, Auntie-in-Law.

37
00:04:07,905 --> 00:04:10,945
Nueng, I told you not to call me that.

38
00:04:11,025 --> 00:04:13,065
We're the same age.
It makes me sound old, got it?

39
00:04:13,145 --> 00:04:17,745
I'm just being respectful, Auntie Pafun.

40
00:04:19,665 --> 00:04:21,905
That hurt.

41
00:04:22,665 --> 00:04:23,865
That was too hard.

42
00:04:25,345 --> 00:04:29,065
You always tease her. You're friends.

43
00:04:33,145 --> 00:04:34,105
Oh.

44
00:04:34,825 --> 00:04:36,185
Morning, Aunt Wee.

45
00:04:36,825 --> 00:04:39,505
Morning. Morning.

46
00:04:39,585 --> 00:04:41,505
-Morning.
-Good morning.

47
00:04:43,985 --> 00:04:47,345
Oon, Fun, and…

48
00:04:47,425 --> 00:04:48,865
This is Nubnueng,

49
00:04:48,945 --> 00:04:53,185
my relative.
This is Aunt Chawee, our neighbor.

50
00:04:53,265 --> 00:04:54,745
Hello, Aunt Chawee.

51
00:04:54,825 --> 00:04:55,825
Hello.

52
00:04:56,505 --> 00:04:57,465
Eh?

53
00:04:59,505 --> 00:05:03,065
Are you staying for a few days?
I see two light green suitcases.

54
00:05:04,305 --> 00:05:08,065
Aunt Wee, were you watering the plants?
I heard water running.

55
00:05:08,145 --> 00:05:09,545
Oh, right, I…

56
00:05:11,185 --> 00:05:15,105
The water! The Metropolitan Waterworks
is going to call me. I left it running.

57
00:05:15,185 --> 00:05:16,625
I'll go take care of it first.

58
00:05:16,705 --> 00:05:20,945
I'll go first. Don't call me.

59
00:05:21,025 --> 00:05:22,505
-Come on, let's go inside.
-Let's go.

60
00:05:22,585 --> 00:05:23,705
Oh, alright.

61
00:05:33,785 --> 00:05:36,825
I think
that auntie next door is kinda weird.

62
00:05:37,665 --> 00:05:41,025
Weird but nice. Don't mind her.

63
00:05:41,105 --> 00:05:42,065
Yeah.

64
00:05:42,145 --> 00:05:46,425
She's actually sweet.
Sometimes, she gets our packages

65
00:05:46,505 --> 00:05:48,185
or waters our plants.

66
00:05:49,105 --> 00:05:50,425
-Really?
-Yeah.

67
00:05:50,505 --> 00:05:52,025
Does she live alone?

68
00:05:52,105 --> 00:05:53,865
With her niece.

69
00:05:53,945 --> 00:05:56,985
By the way, why didn't you tell us
you were coming back?

70
00:05:57,585 --> 00:05:58,545
Hmm?

71
00:06:00,345 --> 00:06:03,305
I made a quick decision.
I just came right away.

72
00:06:06,785 --> 00:06:12,065
Nueng, be serious.
Is something wrong? You can tell us.

73
00:06:16,785 --> 00:06:19,985
Well, I've decided
to move back to Thailand.

74
00:06:20,665 --> 00:06:23,025
That's great. You can stay with us.

75
00:06:23,985 --> 00:06:26,145
Yeah, we have plenty of rooms.

76
00:06:37,185 --> 00:06:39,825
Well, we can talk about that later.

77
00:06:39,905 --> 00:06:44,265
Right now,
we should celebrate your return.

78
00:06:46,065 --> 00:06:46,905
Sure.

79
00:06:49,825 --> 00:06:52,145
Wow, that's a lot.

80
00:06:52,225 --> 00:06:53,305
Come on.

81
00:06:54,905 --> 00:06:56,345
Looks so good.

82
00:06:57,065 --> 00:06:59,305
I ordered a big meal for you.

83
00:06:59,385 --> 00:07:03,025
Didn't know if you've had
spicy food like this over there.

84
00:07:05,185 --> 00:07:06,985
This place is really good.

85
00:07:07,065 --> 00:07:08,465
-Really?
-Yeah.

86
00:07:09,105 --> 00:07:12,465
-Let's eat.
-Go ahead.

87
00:07:14,065 --> 00:07:15,425
Extra fermented fish.

88
00:07:19,305 --> 00:07:20,825
Let's go.

89
00:07:37,225 --> 00:07:38,265
-Nueng.
-Bathroom.

90
00:07:38,345 --> 00:07:40,825
-Bathroom! Bathroom!
-Right here.

91
00:07:44,665 --> 00:07:45,745
Are you okay?

92
00:07:45,825 --> 00:07:46,985
Thanks.

93
00:07:52,385 --> 00:07:53,665
What's wrong with you?

94
00:07:54,345 --> 00:07:55,745
Are you sick, Nueng?

95
00:07:56,345 --> 00:07:59,185
Is that why you came back to Thailand?
For treatment?

96
00:08:00,625 --> 00:08:03,545
Nueng, whatever it is,

97
00:08:04,825 --> 00:08:06,385
we can take care of you, okay?

98
00:08:10,865 --> 00:08:11,825
You two…

99
00:08:13,505 --> 00:08:15,105
I'm not sick.

100
00:08:19,665 --> 00:08:21,105
I'm just pregnant.

101
00:08:22,625 --> 00:08:23,905
Pregnant?

102
00:08:30,065 --> 00:08:34,705
Wait, did your boyfriend
come back with you?

103
00:08:39,385 --> 00:08:40,664
I messed up.

104
00:08:42,024 --> 00:08:45,345
At first, it was just a one-night stand
that almost turned into something more.

105
00:08:47,145 --> 00:08:48,665
But then I found out…

106
00:08:53,265 --> 00:08:57,425
he already has a wife and kids,
and I don't want to ruin anyone's family.

107
00:09:01,545 --> 00:09:05,465
That's awful. He already has a family,
yet he still messed with you?

108
00:09:07,545 --> 00:09:09,145
When I first found out I was pregnant,

109
00:09:11,145 --> 00:09:12,225
I was confused.

110
00:09:14,425 --> 00:09:17,905
But in the end,

111
00:09:19,465 --> 00:09:21,105
I chose to keep the baby.

112
00:09:23,145 --> 00:09:27,385
And I decided to move back to Thailand,
take design jobs here and there…

113
00:09:28,985 --> 00:09:32,345
but right now, I guess I need
to figure out where to settle first.

114
00:09:32,425 --> 00:09:35,745
And where are you supposed to settle?
Just stay here with us.

115
00:09:35,825 --> 00:09:38,225
Yeah, just like old times.

116
00:09:38,305 --> 00:09:40,545
Especially now that you're pregnant,
about to have a baby,

117
00:09:40,625 --> 00:09:43,345
come live with us,
and we'll take care of you.

118
00:09:44,425 --> 00:09:49,585
Would that really be okay?
How could I just move in as a third wheel?

119
00:09:49,665 --> 00:09:51,385
Of course it would be okay.

120
00:09:51,465 --> 00:09:55,225
I've always seen you as family,
never as anything else.

121
00:09:55,825 --> 00:09:57,105
Yeah.

122
00:09:57,185 --> 00:09:59,625
You are family.

123
00:10:01,785 --> 00:10:04,145
I see you two as family too.

124
00:10:04,825 --> 00:10:09,345
At first, I was thinking I'd come back,
buy a condo

125
00:10:09,425 --> 00:10:11,785
and just live there as a mother and child.

126
00:10:13,465 --> 00:10:15,665
Then go buy one.

127
00:10:15,745 --> 00:10:16,985
We'll move in with you.

128
00:10:17,065 --> 00:10:18,745
Yeah, do it.

129
00:10:18,825 --> 00:10:22,305
Wait, what? Then how big a condo
would I have to buy?

130
00:10:22,385 --> 00:10:23,465
Oh?

131
00:10:24,145 --> 00:10:25,545
Exactly.

132
00:10:25,625 --> 00:10:27,905
So just move in here with us.
Problem solved.

133
00:10:29,305 --> 00:10:30,505
No need to buy anything.

134
00:10:39,625 --> 00:10:40,905
Fine, fine.

135
00:10:41,465 --> 00:10:43,505
I'll stay. But…

136
00:10:45,105 --> 00:10:46,065
Are you staying or not?

137
00:10:47,305 --> 00:10:49,345
Yes, yes. I'm staying.

138
00:10:49,425 --> 00:10:50,625
That's all it took.

139
00:10:52,905 --> 00:10:56,105
And have you told my mom yet?
About coming back to Thailand?

140
00:10:56,185 --> 00:10:59,185
Of course I told her.
She's basically my godmother.

141
00:11:00,425 --> 00:11:04,145
Ever since my parents died, Aunt Prang

142
00:11:04,225 --> 00:11:06,425
has been
the only elder relative I have left.

143
00:11:07,625 --> 00:11:09,145
She knows everything.

144
00:11:09,225 --> 00:11:12,225
She knows all of it.
I just told her not to tell you two yet.

145
00:11:14,545 --> 00:11:17,825
Tomorrow, I'm going back home to see her.

146
00:11:19,425 --> 00:11:21,825
Then I'll drive you there myself.

147
00:11:21,905 --> 00:11:25,425
No need. You just keep working.
She already booked me a van.

148
00:11:25,505 --> 00:11:27,585
But you're pregnant.

149
00:11:28,465 --> 00:11:31,265
Hey, I'm just pregnant.

150
00:11:31,345 --> 00:11:32,585
I can still take care of myself.

151
00:11:33,665 --> 00:11:34,745
I'm fine.

152
00:11:34,825 --> 00:11:37,505
And then you're coming back here
to live with us.

153
00:12:05,305 --> 00:12:07,545
KRIT (OLD FRIEND)

154
00:12:14,425 --> 00:12:15,625
Yes, Krit?

155
00:12:15,705 --> 00:12:16,545
<i>Fun.</i>

156
00:12:17,145 --> 00:12:21,225
The client meeting this afternoon,
they want to move it to six. Are you free?

157
00:12:22,185 --> 00:12:23,385
Six?

158
00:12:24,545 --> 00:12:27,745
Yes, that works.

159
00:12:27,825 --> 00:12:29,225
<i>I'll send you the location.</i>

160
00:12:32,305 --> 00:12:35,105
What area is it?
I'll pick the place myself.

161
00:12:37,225 --> 00:12:40,265
Fine. Around Srinakarin.

162
00:12:40,345 --> 00:12:41,825
Srinakarin?

163
00:12:42,985 --> 00:12:46,385
There's a new cafe around there,
near Suan Luang Rama IX.

164
00:12:46,465 --> 00:12:47,985
The atmosphere is nice,
good for discussing work.

165
00:12:48,065 --> 00:12:49,665
<i>I'll send you the location.</i>

166
00:12:50,825 --> 00:12:52,145
See you this evening.

167
00:12:52,865 --> 00:12:54,305
Alright.

168
00:13:06,705 --> 00:13:07,545
Yes?

169
00:13:07,625 --> 00:13:08,505
<i>Oon-Oon.</i>

170
00:13:08,585 --> 00:13:11,825
I have a client meeting tonight at six.

171
00:13:13,625 --> 00:13:16,105
The client isn't that Krit guy again,
is it?

172
00:13:17,185 --> 00:13:18,225
<i>It is.</i>

173
00:13:19,105 --> 00:13:20,145
Krit again.

174
00:13:21,985 --> 00:13:23,465
I'll finish the meeting
and come right back, okay?

175
00:13:23,545 --> 00:13:24,825
Okay.

176
00:13:27,665 --> 00:13:32,505
Fun, when you get dressed,
video call me first, okay?

177
00:13:33,105 --> 00:13:34,745
Why? You can just tell me now.

178
00:13:34,825 --> 00:13:37,505
That's all for now. I'm driving.

179
00:13:37,585 --> 00:13:39,025
<i>Okay.</i>

180
00:14:01,665 --> 00:14:03,105
Yes, Oon?

181
00:14:03,185 --> 00:14:06,905
Fun, can you put your phone down?

182
00:14:08,185 --> 00:14:09,185
Hang up?

183
00:14:09,265 --> 00:14:13,985
No, I mean put it on the dressing table.

184
00:14:14,065 --> 00:14:16,345
Oh, okay.

185
00:14:21,665 --> 00:14:22,625
PAFUN

186
00:14:22,705 --> 00:14:24,345
Can you step back?

187
00:14:24,425 --> 00:14:25,505
<i>Step back?</i>

188
00:14:26,145 --> 00:14:27,225
Yes.

189
00:14:30,345 --> 00:14:32,705
Fun, stand up.

190
00:14:35,425 --> 00:14:38,505
And move the chair away.

191
00:14:44,745 --> 00:14:46,345
And step back a little more.

192
00:14:47,505 --> 00:14:50,585
A bit more.

193
00:14:52,705 --> 00:14:54,065
This outfit won't work.

194
00:14:55,305 --> 00:14:57,065
This one?

195
00:14:57,145 --> 00:14:58,225
<i>Yes.</i>

196
00:14:58,305 --> 00:14:59,505
<i>I…</i>

197
00:14:59,585 --> 00:15:00,825
AIOON

198
00:15:00,905 --> 00:15:03,665
<i>I remember you've worn it a lot.</i>

199
00:15:03,745 --> 00:15:04,905
Huh?

200
00:15:04,985 --> 00:15:07,265
This one? A lot?

201
00:15:07,345 --> 00:15:08,505
<i>Yes.</i>

202
00:15:08,585 --> 00:15:12,305
<i>Why don't you change?</i>

203
00:15:18,065 --> 00:15:19,345
Okay.

204
00:15:24,505 --> 00:15:26,345
This outfit doesn't work either.

205
00:15:28,545 --> 00:15:29,665
Why not?

206
00:15:30,345 --> 00:15:33,505
Well, you get cold easily.

207
00:15:33,585 --> 00:15:38,505
And the top doesn't match the pants.

208
00:15:39,465 --> 00:15:41,945
-Doesn't match?
-<i>Yeah.</i>

209
00:15:43,785 --> 00:15:49,025
<i>How about you show me your wardrobe?</i>

210
00:15:49,105 --> 00:15:50,465
<i>I'll pick for you.</i>

211
00:15:52,025 --> 00:15:53,025
Okay.

212
00:16:05,745 --> 00:16:08,225
Closer.

213
00:16:10,785 --> 00:16:12,825
That one, the third one.

214
00:16:13,945 --> 00:16:15,265
This one?

215
00:16:15,345 --> 00:16:17,465
No, not that.

216
00:16:18,905 --> 00:16:20,385
How about this one?

217
00:16:24,585 --> 00:16:27,185
Put it back. No.

218
00:16:28,465 --> 00:16:31,905
I think you should check another wardrobe.

219
00:16:35,905 --> 00:16:37,465
Just go one by one.

220
00:16:39,745 --> 00:16:40,785
One by one.

221
00:16:43,585 --> 00:16:44,545
Yeah.

222
00:16:44,625 --> 00:16:46,465
-This one?
-<i>Yes.</i>

223
00:16:48,305 --> 00:16:49,665
This one?

224
00:16:49,745 --> 00:16:50,665
Yes.

225
00:16:50,745 --> 00:16:53,625
That one's perfect.

226
00:16:55,785 --> 00:16:56,785
Okay.

227
00:17:00,625 --> 00:17:02,145
Zip it up.

228
00:17:05,464 --> 00:17:07,385
Okay, perfect.

229
00:17:08,785 --> 00:17:09,825
Oon,

230
00:17:09,905 --> 00:17:12,825
I feel like it doesn't match at all.

231
00:17:12,905 --> 00:17:15,224
The shirt and the pants don't match.

232
00:17:15,305 --> 00:17:17,025
<i>No, I think</i>

233
00:17:17,105 --> 00:17:19,145
this is the new trend.

234
00:17:19,785 --> 00:17:22,224
I don't think so.

235
00:17:26,905 --> 00:17:30,665
Do I really not have anything to wear?

236
00:17:31,265 --> 00:17:33,545
It's so hard to choose.

237
00:17:36,425 --> 00:17:40,665
Maybe you should let me buy new clothes.

238
00:17:41,305 --> 00:17:42,505
Huh?

239
00:17:44,625 --> 00:17:47,425
Okay, you can buy new ones.

240
00:17:47,505 --> 00:17:48,945
How many?

241
00:17:49,025 --> 00:17:50,825
<i>You've rejected</i>

242
00:17:50,905 --> 00:17:52,745
quite a few already.

243
00:17:52,825 --> 00:17:56,505
Not including those
you said I've worn too often.

244
00:17:56,585 --> 00:17:59,945
As many as you want.

245
00:18:00,025 --> 00:18:02,865
Thank you. I'll go change again.

246
00:18:02,945 --> 00:18:04,665
I'm sure you'll definitely like it.

247
00:18:08,705 --> 00:18:11,545
<i>How is it? Do you like it?</i>

248
00:18:11,625 --> 00:18:15,025
<i>Fully covered.</i>

249
00:18:15,105 --> 00:18:16,665
Okay.

250
00:18:17,745 --> 00:18:20,185
Don't forget what you said.

251
00:18:20,265 --> 00:18:23,025
As many new clothes as I want.

252
00:18:25,145 --> 00:18:29,065
-Yes.
-Oon, I'll go now. I'm running late.

253
00:18:33,545 --> 00:18:35,945
New collection.

254
00:18:36,905 --> 00:18:38,385
As many as you want…

255
00:18:55,785 --> 00:18:57,625
DELIVERY PARKING AREA

256
00:19:00,385 --> 00:19:03,065
Excuse me, can I park here?

257
00:19:03,145 --> 00:19:04,625
I'm dining at the restaurant.

258
00:19:04,705 --> 00:19:06,905
This is a delivery spot,

259
00:19:06,985 --> 00:19:09,705
but there are no deliveries right now.
You can park here.

260
00:19:09,785 --> 00:19:12,145
Thank you.
Please let me know if I need to move it.

261
00:19:12,225 --> 00:19:13,425
-Sure.
-Thank you.

262
00:19:13,505 --> 00:19:14,345
Please come in.

263
00:19:14,985 --> 00:19:16,105
This way, please.

264
00:19:36,945 --> 00:19:38,985
Here, let me carry that.

265
00:19:39,065 --> 00:19:40,505
It's okay, I've got it.

266
00:19:41,905 --> 00:19:42,945
Wait.

267
00:19:43,985 --> 00:19:46,625
Can we talk first?
The client isn't here yet.

268
00:19:47,265 --> 00:19:48,505
What is it?

269
00:19:50,505 --> 00:19:51,905
You're really hardworking.

270
00:19:52,625 --> 00:19:54,705
Beautiful and efficient too.

271
00:19:54,785 --> 00:19:57,785
If I introduce more clients,
you'd take them, right?

272
00:19:58,465 --> 00:20:01,425
Of course. I always give my all at work.

273
00:20:02,105 --> 00:20:06,585
Actually, I don't want you to work hard.
I want you to live more comfortably.

274
00:20:10,105 --> 00:20:12,185
I know you're married.

275
00:20:13,385 --> 00:20:16,905
I'm just offering you a good option,

276
00:20:16,985 --> 00:20:18,585
a life where you don't have to struggle.

277
00:20:19,705 --> 00:20:21,265
A house, a car,

278
00:20:21,345 --> 00:20:24,745
anything you want, I can give it to you.

279
00:20:25,985 --> 00:20:27,585
You don't have to leave Aioon,

280
00:20:29,425 --> 00:20:31,345
but when I call,

281
00:20:31,425 --> 00:20:33,105
you come.

282
00:20:41,585 --> 00:20:43,905
I already know how you feel about me.

283
00:20:46,385 --> 00:20:50,225
Let me be clear. There's no way
anything will ever happen between us.

284
00:20:50,305 --> 00:20:52,825
If it was meant to happen,
it wouldn't have taken this long.

285
00:20:53,785 --> 00:20:56,945
I've never thought of you that way,
and I never will.

286
00:21:01,545 --> 00:21:04,825
I'll finish this project,
so it doesn't affect my company.

287
00:21:06,065 --> 00:21:08,185
But if you keep thinking like this,

288
00:21:08,785 --> 00:21:10,985
this will be the last project
I ever do with you.

289
00:21:18,105 --> 00:21:19,665
You're going to regret this.

290
00:21:23,465 --> 00:21:26,345
Then I'll go with this fabric shade,

291
00:21:26,425 --> 00:21:28,465
so it matches the tile you selected.

292
00:21:29,585 --> 00:21:31,385
That works. The color is nice.

293
00:21:31,465 --> 00:21:32,425
Alright.

294
00:21:32,505 --> 00:21:38,945
And for the counter and wall tones,

295
00:21:39,025 --> 00:21:40,945
I suggest

296
00:21:41,025 --> 00:21:44,785
these two shades, so everything matches
and has the same mood and tone.

297
00:21:44,865 --> 00:21:46,585
Light tones are nice. They look clean.

298
00:21:46,665 --> 00:21:48,465
Excuse me, ma'am.

299
00:21:48,545 --> 00:21:52,065
Could you move your car?
A delivery truck just arrived.

300
00:21:52,145 --> 00:21:54,345
Oh, can I have a moment?

301
00:21:56,185 --> 00:21:57,665
I'll move it for you.

302
00:21:57,745 --> 00:21:59,745
Please continue your meeting.

303
00:22:02,025 --> 00:22:03,385
Would you like the clients to wait?

304
00:22:10,025 --> 00:22:11,305
Thank you.

305
00:22:24,465 --> 00:22:25,905
Where were we?

306
00:22:25,985 --> 00:22:30,025
For the wall and counter tones,

307
00:22:30,105 --> 00:22:32,945
we'll follow this mood and tone.

308
00:22:33,025 --> 00:22:34,825
Just like the reference.

309
00:22:35,705 --> 00:22:36,825
This way, please.

310
00:23:13,745 --> 00:23:14,865
This way, please.

311
00:23:18,465 --> 00:23:21,505
-You can just send me off here.
-Sure.

312
00:23:22,305 --> 00:23:23,585
Goodbye.

313
00:23:24,185 --> 00:23:25,385
Thank you.

314
00:23:28,305 --> 00:23:29,385
Fun.

315
00:23:34,185 --> 00:23:35,345
Fun.

316
00:23:35,425 --> 00:23:37,025
I'm sorry.

317
00:23:38,145 --> 00:23:40,225
I just wanted you to know how I feel.

318
00:23:41,785 --> 00:23:44,345
I didn't have a choice
since you're married.

319
00:23:46,185 --> 00:23:47,545
But now I understand.

320
00:23:49,625 --> 00:23:51,865
I'll go back to being your good friend.

321
00:23:55,305 --> 00:23:58,945
Okay. I hope you can do as you say.

322
00:24:27,025 --> 00:24:28,945
Oon-Oon.

323
00:24:30,785 --> 00:24:32,225
You're home late.

324
00:24:36,745 --> 00:24:38,505
Have you eaten?

325
00:24:39,625 --> 00:24:42,785
Yes. Alone.

326
00:24:45,465 --> 00:24:48,025
But I bought something for you.
Want me to heat it up?

327
00:24:48,865 --> 00:24:50,145
It's okay.

328
00:24:56,585 --> 00:24:57,905
Nice outfit.

329
00:25:02,025 --> 00:25:04,185
I'll go shower first.

330
00:25:45,465 --> 00:25:48,945
<i>Oon-Oon! Come upstairs now! Right now!</i>

331
00:25:49,665 --> 00:25:51,225
What? Fun?

332
00:27:24,225 --> 00:27:25,705
You're not mad anymore?

333
00:27:26,545 --> 00:27:29,385
No. Not anymore.

334
00:27:30,185 --> 00:27:31,585
Not jealous anymore?

335
00:27:34,425 --> 00:27:35,665
Still jealous.

336
00:27:38,745 --> 00:27:42,265
Thank you for making me feel valued.

337
00:28:03,705 --> 00:28:06,465
KRIT (OLD FRIEND)

338
00:28:10,145 --> 00:28:13,425
Aren't you going to answer?
What if it's important?

339
00:28:16,105 --> 00:28:19,225
No. You're more important.

340
00:28:54,105 --> 00:28:56,345
MS. WIRINYA SRIPITICHOTE

341
00:29:13,105 --> 00:29:15,465
MS. WIRINYA SRIPITICHOTE

342
00:29:15,545 --> 00:29:19,225
MS. PAFUN SETTANUN

343
00:29:30,305 --> 00:29:31,425
Yes, Mr. Krit?

344
00:29:31,505 --> 00:29:33,905
Get me the contact
for that paint company from last week.

345
00:29:35,505 --> 00:29:37,985
Which one, sir?

346
00:29:38,065 --> 00:29:41,065
That's your job to find out.
The one that just came recently.

347
00:29:41,145 --> 00:29:42,705
Go find it!

348
00:29:42,785 --> 00:29:44,625
Yes, sir.

349
00:30:10,305 --> 00:30:11,785
Hello, Ms. Boom.

350
00:30:11,865 --> 00:30:13,145
Oh.

351
00:30:13,225 --> 00:30:17,025
Hello, Ms. Wirinya.
Do you have a site visit today?

352
00:30:18,945 --> 00:30:24,745
Let me check if the foreman is back
from lunch. Please have a seat.

353
00:30:24,825 --> 00:30:26,145
Thank you.

354
00:30:37,105 --> 00:30:39,425
INVOICE

355
00:31:29,025 --> 00:31:31,065
-Hello, Ms. Wirinya.
-Hello.

356
00:31:31,145 --> 00:31:32,425
Here to check the site?

357
00:31:34,625 --> 00:31:35,745
Please.

358
00:31:44,505 --> 00:31:46,025
Have you looked into hospitals yet?

359
00:31:49,625 --> 00:31:51,865
If not, want to use the one I found?

360
00:31:52,665 --> 00:31:53,545
-Here.
-Sure.

361
00:31:54,065 --> 00:31:58,465
This one has lots of good reviews,
skilled doctors

362
00:31:58,545 --> 00:32:00,745
and it's close to our house.

363
00:32:00,825 --> 00:32:02,345
Oh, really?

364
00:32:02,945 --> 00:32:05,785
Look, reviews from moms.

365
00:32:05,865 --> 00:32:06,905
Yeah.

366
00:32:07,785 --> 00:32:09,505
I'm home.

367
00:32:09,585 --> 00:32:10,905
What are you two up to?

368
00:32:11,705 --> 00:32:13,265
We're looking for a maternity hospital.

369
00:32:16,985 --> 00:32:19,585
So, how do you want to give birth?

370
00:32:20,505 --> 00:32:23,105
Naturally.

371
00:32:24,105 --> 00:32:24,985
Good.

372
00:32:26,265 --> 00:32:29,545
So, are you okay with this place?

373
00:32:29,625 --> 00:32:33,065
Yeah, I actually had this one in mind too.

374
00:32:33,145 --> 00:32:34,865
Then I'll take you there myself.

375
00:32:38,305 --> 00:32:40,945
Look. I'll show you that
there are a lot of skilled doctors.

376
00:32:41,025 --> 00:32:43,145
Here.

377
00:32:43,225 --> 00:32:44,785
Look at this one.

378
00:32:44,865 --> 00:32:45,945
Fun.

379
00:32:46,705 --> 00:32:49,705
What kind of person is Mr. Kritsana?

380
00:32:53,225 --> 00:32:54,745
Well…

381
00:32:54,825 --> 00:32:58,905
Back then, he was fine.
But now, I'm not so sure.

382
00:32:59,625 --> 00:33:02,545
From working with him,
I don't think he's that great.

383
00:33:03,305 --> 00:33:07,265
Not great? In what way?

384
00:33:08,505 --> 00:33:12,945
Work-wise, he's okay.
But personally, he's not.

385
00:33:13,785 --> 00:33:15,945
He's

386
00:33:16,025 --> 00:33:20,385
extremely confident. Way too confident.
It's uncomfortable being around him.

387
00:33:25,265 --> 00:33:28,625
Why? Did he do anything to you?

388
00:33:29,265 --> 00:33:31,545
No, not yet.

389
00:33:31,625 --> 00:33:36,225
Why'd you ask it like that?
Has he done something to you?

390
00:33:38,025 --> 00:33:39,105
Well,

391
00:33:39,705 --> 00:33:40,745
just a little.

392
00:33:41,465 --> 00:33:43,145
But I can handle it.

393
00:33:43,225 --> 00:33:46,065
After this project,
I won't work with him again.

394
00:33:47,105 --> 00:33:48,745
What did he do?

395
00:33:52,465 --> 00:33:53,465
Well,

396
00:33:54,785 --> 00:33:56,785
he just said some inappropriate things.

397
00:34:00,625 --> 00:34:03,025
Is he the guy you told me about?

398
00:34:03,105 --> 00:34:04,865
The childhood friend
who's now your client,

399
00:34:04,945 --> 00:34:06,225
right?

400
00:34:06,305 --> 00:34:07,345
Yeah.

401
00:34:07,425 --> 00:34:08,744
That guy?

402
00:34:09,385 --> 00:34:11,585
If I see him…

403
00:34:14,304 --> 00:34:16,705
Don't get mad, Mommy.

404
00:34:17,744 --> 00:34:20,304
If you hate someone,
your baby might end up looking like them.

405
00:34:22,065 --> 00:34:24,505
Oh, right. I forgot.

406
00:34:24,585 --> 00:34:26,545
Okay, let's try again.

407
00:34:27,185 --> 00:34:29,344
I love him.

408
00:34:29,425 --> 00:34:30,264
What?

409
00:34:30,344 --> 00:34:31,185
Hey.

410
00:34:31,264 --> 00:34:33,665
I love him so much.

411
00:34:33,744 --> 00:34:34,585
Ouch!

412
00:34:34,665 --> 00:34:36,264
-What?
-What happened?

413
00:34:36,344 --> 00:34:37,545
-What happened?
-What's wrong?

414
00:34:38,385 --> 00:34:39,425
The baby kicked.

415
00:34:39,505 --> 00:34:41,185
Huh?

416
00:34:41,264 --> 00:34:43,264
Can I feel?

417
00:34:44,625 --> 00:34:46,105
Where? Can I feel?

418
00:34:46,185 --> 00:34:47,585
Where?

419
00:34:48,225 --> 00:34:50,065
I want to feel it too.

420
00:34:50,665 --> 00:34:51,865
Fun.

421
00:34:54,105 --> 00:34:55,744
Share her with me too.

422
00:34:56,665 --> 00:34:58,905
Where?

423
00:34:59,545 --> 00:35:01,505
I can't feel anything.

424
00:35:01,585 --> 00:35:03,785
-Where? Did you feel anything?
-Where?

425
00:35:03,865 --> 00:35:04,985
I can't feel anything.

426
00:35:05,065 --> 00:35:06,345
Oh.

427
00:35:06,425 --> 00:35:07,825
-Did you feel it?
-No.

428
00:35:10,665 --> 00:35:12,305
Where is it?

429
00:35:13,785 --> 00:35:15,065
-Do you feel it?
-No.

430
00:35:24,385 --> 00:35:25,625
The heartbeat is strong.

431
00:35:26,225 --> 00:35:28,785
Overall growth looks good,

432
00:35:28,865 --> 00:35:32,345
and today's ultrasound
is within the normal range.

433
00:35:32,425 --> 00:35:35,985
So today, you pass.

434
00:35:52,065 --> 00:35:55,105
TRANSFER/WITHDRAWAL
30,000 BAHT

435
00:35:57,145 --> 00:35:58,545
What money is this?

436
00:35:58,625 --> 00:36:00,625
TRANSFER/WITHDRAWAL
30,000 BAHT

437
00:36:02,465 --> 00:36:04,385
Hey, Oon, come take a look at this.

438
00:36:04,465 --> 00:36:06,105
Okay.

439
00:36:09,305 --> 00:36:11,665
Can we remove this beam?

440
00:36:11,745 --> 00:36:13,985
It'd look better without it.

441
00:36:15,025 --> 00:36:17,225
Then why didn't you design it better
in the first place?

442
00:36:19,105 --> 00:36:22,465
So you wouldn't be out of work.
Come on, help me out.

443
00:36:22,545 --> 00:36:23,825
Fine, let's do it.

444
00:36:23,905 --> 00:36:24,825
Alright.

445
00:36:29,265 --> 00:36:30,465
Here.

446
00:36:38,985 --> 00:36:40,665
Oh.

447
00:36:40,745 --> 00:36:42,505
Are you out jogging?

448
00:36:42,585 --> 00:36:43,945
-Hello.
-Hi.

449
00:36:44,025 --> 00:36:47,745
I'm just getting some fresh air
and doing some light exercise.

450
00:36:47,825 --> 00:36:49,265
I see.

451
00:36:53,145 --> 00:36:55,545
What's wrong? Feeling bloated?

452
00:36:55,625 --> 00:36:58,745
You don't exercise enough.

453
00:36:58,825 --> 00:37:00,745
Actually…

454
00:37:01,905 --> 00:37:03,825
I'm pregnant.

455
00:37:09,305 --> 00:37:12,825
Please don't mind me asking.

456
00:37:12,905 --> 00:37:16,625
I've never seen the baby's father.
Where is he?

457
00:37:16,705 --> 00:37:20,265
Well…

458
00:37:24,065 --> 00:37:27,385
Hearing your story,
I can tell you're so strong.

459
00:37:28,105 --> 00:37:29,385
But it's fine.

460
00:37:31,665 --> 00:37:34,425
Women these days can do anything.

461
00:37:34,505 --> 00:37:38,065
If you ever have a problem,
you can always talk to me. Okay?

462
00:37:38,945 --> 00:37:40,425
Thank you.

463
00:37:49,305 --> 00:37:53,625
Do you have any protective charms
for you and the baby yet?

464
00:38:31,345 --> 00:38:33,785
Aunt Wee, I'll return this for now.

465
00:38:33,865 --> 00:38:35,945
If I need it later, I'll come ask again.

466
00:38:36,025 --> 00:38:38,985
Oh, no need to return it.
Keep it. It brings good luck.

467
00:38:39,065 --> 00:38:41,665
It's okay. You keep it. Thank you.

468
00:38:41,745 --> 00:38:44,865
Then do this.
If you ever need one, tell me.

469
00:38:44,945 --> 00:38:48,985
I have many, for all kinds of luck. Look.

470
00:38:49,065 --> 00:38:52,665
Here.

471
00:38:54,265 --> 00:38:56,585
Anyway, let's keep in touch.

472
00:38:56,665 --> 00:38:57,945
Okay, see you.

473
00:38:58,785 --> 00:39:00,105
See you.

474
00:39:06,865 --> 00:39:07,705
Aioon,

475
00:39:07,785 --> 00:39:11,945
why did you design this beam so big?
And there are too many columns.

476
00:39:12,025 --> 00:39:15,585
Did you even check if your design
is structurally possible?

477
00:39:15,665 --> 00:39:18,305
Without these columns,
how would it support the structure?

478
00:39:18,385 --> 00:39:21,785
But it's design. Design, you know?

479
00:39:21,865 --> 00:39:22,945
-And you--
-Stop.

480
00:39:25,825 --> 00:39:26,745
Yes?

481
00:39:26,825 --> 00:39:27,905
<i>Ms. Wirinya.</i>

482
00:39:27,985 --> 00:39:29,985
Come to the meeting room now.

483
00:39:31,265 --> 00:39:32,225
Yes.

484
00:39:36,425 --> 00:39:37,985
Nu just called me in.

485
00:39:39,065 --> 00:39:41,985
But something feels off.

486
00:39:47,225 --> 00:39:48,065
It's Nu.

487
00:39:49,905 --> 00:39:51,305
Yes, Nu?

488
00:39:51,385 --> 00:39:53,785
<i>Mr. Thanwa, come to the meeting room.</i>

489
00:39:53,865 --> 00:39:55,305
Yes.

490
00:39:58,665 --> 00:40:01,945
My call was weird too.
He even used my full name.

491
00:40:06,345 --> 00:40:07,825
What does this mean?

492
00:40:08,385 --> 00:40:10,865
Can either of you explain?

493
00:40:25,585 --> 00:40:29,865
WIRINYA SRIPITICHOTE

494
00:40:29,945 --> 00:40:31,385
30,000 BAHT

495
00:40:39,265 --> 00:40:42,305
TRANSFER/WITHDRAWAL
30,000 BAHT

496
00:40:44,305 --> 00:40:45,785
What money is this?

497
00:40:48,625 --> 00:40:51,065
Nu, I don't know anything about this.

498
00:40:51,145 --> 00:40:56,105
With evidence this clear,
how can you deny it?

499
00:41:00,785 --> 00:41:04,025
Did you two really collude
over this amount of money?

500
00:41:05,385 --> 00:41:07,705
No, Nu.

501
00:41:07,785 --> 00:41:12,225
Mr. Kritsana was the one who told me
to add that company to the vendor list.

502
00:41:13,665 --> 00:41:15,705
Where's the memo? The memo?!

503
00:41:21,785 --> 00:41:24,585
-This is it, right?
-Yeah. Okay.

504
00:41:32,185 --> 00:41:33,505
Hello, Mr. Kritsana.

505
00:41:34,425 --> 00:41:35,545
<i>Mr. Thanwa.</i>

506
00:41:35,625 --> 00:41:39,345
Please add the Tough Paint company
to the vendor list.

507
00:41:39,425 --> 00:41:42,665
I'll send the memo later. It's urgent.

508
00:41:42,745 --> 00:41:43,985
Got it.

509
00:41:48,505 --> 00:41:49,665
Nu.

510
00:41:52,385 --> 00:41:54,105
You know us.

511
00:41:59,945 --> 00:42:01,745
And so what?

512
00:42:02,345 --> 00:42:04,065
The evidence is clear.

513
00:42:10,705 --> 00:42:12,945
Please give us time to prove it.

514
00:42:17,905 --> 00:42:19,945
You have four days.

515
00:42:21,385 --> 00:42:23,505
Find proof.

516
00:42:25,265 --> 00:42:29,585
Otherwise, you're both terminated.

517
00:42:31,545 --> 00:42:32,545
Understood?

518
00:42:34,345 --> 00:42:35,465
-Yes.
-Yes.

519
00:42:35,985 --> 00:42:38,145
You're suspended starting today.

520
00:42:39,745 --> 00:42:43,745
Can I take photos of these documents?

521
00:43:07,465 --> 00:43:08,905
What's wrong with her?

522
00:43:12,305 --> 00:43:15,985
Morning sickness. She felt dizzy.

523
00:43:16,065 --> 00:43:18,185
She took some medicine and fell asleep.

524
00:43:21,025 --> 00:43:23,545
There's <i>rad na.</i> You want to eat?

525
00:43:25,345 --> 00:43:26,545
Not yet.

526
00:43:27,425 --> 00:43:30,185
I'm not really hungry. I'm tired.

527
00:43:31,145 --> 00:43:33,825
I'll go shower first.

528
00:44:10,465 --> 00:44:14,345
Oon, what's wrong? You can tell me.

529
00:44:19,625 --> 00:44:20,785
It's nothing.

530
00:44:32,625 --> 00:44:34,305
Are you okay?

531
00:44:46,785 --> 00:44:47,945
Fun…

532
00:44:50,065 --> 00:44:51,105
I…

533
00:44:54,105 --> 00:44:57,345
I can't build a future for you anymore.

534
00:44:59,585 --> 00:45:01,905
I've been suspended from work.

535
00:45:04,145 --> 00:45:06,305
Nu accused me of embezzlement,

536
00:45:07,865 --> 00:45:09,985
but I didn't do it.

537
00:45:10,065 --> 00:45:11,425
I didn't.

538
00:45:13,425 --> 00:45:17,265
Now I can't earn money.
I can't take care of you.

539
00:45:18,425 --> 00:45:19,985
I have nothing left.

540
00:45:20,065 --> 00:45:24,905
I can't do this anymore. I can't. I can't.

541
00:45:26,665 --> 00:45:28,025
I can't do it.

542
00:45:33,745 --> 00:45:34,745
Oon.

543
00:45:36,545 --> 00:45:40,025
It's okay. It's okay.

544
00:45:42,025 --> 00:45:43,545
I can take care of you.

545
00:45:48,825 --> 00:45:51,905
We've been through so much together.

546
00:45:52,585 --> 00:45:54,425
We've faced worse than this.

547
00:45:55,945 --> 00:45:57,785
We started from nothing before.

548
00:45:59,385 --> 00:46:02,145
If we have to start from zero again,
that's okay.

549
00:46:09,065 --> 00:46:12,305
It's not a big deal. We'll get through it.

550
00:46:14,705 --> 00:46:16,145
I'm hardworking, you know.

551
00:46:17,585 --> 00:46:19,025
I can take care of you.

552
00:46:30,665 --> 00:46:34,985
I'm sorry, Fun. I'm sorry.

553
00:46:43,745 --> 00:46:45,425
It's okay.

554
00:46:46,945 --> 00:46:48,305
I love you.

555
00:46:54,905 --> 00:46:56,265
Thank you.

556
00:47:04,345 --> 00:47:06,105
I'm sorry.

557
00:47:42,705 --> 00:47:47,185
About your old offer…
I wonder if you still remember it.

558
00:47:47,265 --> 00:47:49,425
In the end, you chose me.

559
00:47:49,505 --> 00:47:52,665
Once we finish tonight,
you can get your new car tomorrow.

560
00:47:54,665 --> 00:47:56,265
Let me see.

561
00:48:35,945 --> 00:48:38,145
